I have ordered from this restaurant for months via seamless. I always order the same thing, family combo #1, which consists of a whole chicken, rice, beans, salad and a soda. This time I decided to order an extra beans and rice so that I could have some on the following day. My children ate the night it was ordered and when I went to eat it the following day for lunch around noon. I found multiple maggots in both beans. I was extremely disgusted and upset as my children already ate it and I had 1 bite before noticing. When I reported to seamless they called the restaurant and advised them and they stated they would not refund me. Which ultimately wasn’t even what I wanted. I just wanted them to rectify the situation. Seamless did in fact give me a credit on my account. If you chose to order be careful of what you eat.  BTW. I have photos but can not upload them on here.

I came across this place not only because of the cheap prices but because i havent tasted a good plate of rice and beans in a long time. I ordered and it came in 20 mins. The rice was good and filling and the beans were good as well. The tostones were tasty as well. The only issue that i had was that this place is spanish american but more leaning towards the american side. If they put it towards the middle where they have arroz con gandules on the menu or mangu chimis they would be unstoppable. But they were good def going back.
